A '''Jedi hunter''', also known as a '''Jedi killer''', was an individual tasked with the [[hunting]] and [[Death|killing]] of members of the [[Jedi Order]].<ref name="USW">''[[Ultimate Star Wars]]''</ref>

==History==
===Republic Era===
====High Republic Era====
The [[Children of the Storm]] were former [[Force-sensitive]]s, all of whom had been experimented on by [[Baron]] [[Boolan]],<ref name="Eye of Darkness">''[[The High Republic: The Eye of Darkness]]''</ref> who acted as Jedi hunters<ref name="Boolan Databank" /> during the [[Nihil]]s' rule over the [[Occlusion Zone]].<ref name="Eye of Darkness" /> Part of their mission was to capture further Force-sensitives for experimentation.<ref name="Boolan Databank" /> Some Nihil  also served as Jedi hunters under [[General]] [[Abediah Viess]],<ref name="Shadows 2" /> who was a Jedi killer herself, acquiring multiple lightsabers which she presented to the [[Eye of the Nihil]] [[Marchion Ro]] in their first meeting.<ref name="Shadows 4">[[The High Republic – Shadows of Starlight 4|''The High Republic – Shadows of Starlight'' 4]]</ref>

====Late Republic Era====
{{Quote|Listen to me, Jedi. I do not care about your politics. I do not care about your Republic. I only live to see you die!|General Grievous|<ref name="Grievous Intrigue" />}}
[[File:AgeofRepublic-GrievousCoverArt.jpg|left|thumb|250px|During the Clone Wars, Grievous, the leader of the Separatist Alliance army, eliminated many Jedi.]]
[[Nautolan]] pirate queen [[Zilastra]] held a vendetta against the Jedi Order due to Councilman [[Sifo-Dyas]] and, in her adulthood, plotted to unite various pirate factions to help her assassinate the Jedi High Council. She employed gas against Jedi and marks her Jedi kills with a [[Sabacc|sabaac card]] representing "The Idiot" within their mouth. She notably clashed with Jedi Master [[Depa Billaba]] and [[Mace Windu]], developing a fierce enmity with the former.<ref name="The Living Force">''[[The Living Force]]''</ref> 

Thane [[Chulok]] was regarded as a Jedi killer and deadly warrior by Jedi Master [[Qui-Gon Jinn]], who survived a encounter with him. In a post-mortem message, he tasked Mace Windu with protecting the planet [[Metagos]] from his organization, leading to the Jedi Master to eventually confronting him several times before ultimately prevailing and killing him.<ref name="Mace Windu: The Glass Abyss">''[[Mace Windu: The Glass Abyss]]''</ref>

The [[Kaleesh]] [[Supreme Martial Commander of the Separatist Droid Armies|Supreme Commander]] of the [[Confederacy military|Separatist military]] [[General]] [[Grievous]] was trained in the art of [[lightsaber combat]] by [[Count of Serenno|Count]] [[Dooku]] and claimed the [[lightsaber]]s of [[Jedi]] he slew as trophies.<ref name="USW" /> As the [[Clone Wars]] progressed, Grievous garnered a fearsome reputation as a formidable Jedi killer, striking terror into the hearts of [[Galactic Republic|Republic]] citizens.<ref name="CIS history gallery 9">{{Databank|url=confederacy-of-independent-systems-history-gallery|title=Confederacy of Independent Systems History Gallery}} {{C|Image 9 caption}}</ref> Among Grievous' victims included [[Neebo]], [[Nahdar Vebb]],<ref name="LoG">{{TCW|Lair of Grievous}}</ref> a [[Unidentified Mikkian Jedi|Mikkian Jedi]], and a [[Unidentified Jedi Padawan (Grievous)|human Padawan]].<ref name="AoR-GG1">[[Age of Republic - General Grievous 1|''Age of Republic - General Grievous'' 1]]</ref> Like their [[cyborg]] master, the [[IG-100 MagnaGuard]]s were also notorious for being Jedi killers,<ref name="HC 25">{{HelmetCollectionCite|25|Databank A-Z}}</ref> having been specifically constructed to take on [[Jedi Knight]]s.<ref name="Star Wars 9">[[Star Wars (2015) 9|''Star Wars'' (2015) 9]]</ref>

[[Bounty hunter]]s were also sometimes employed as Jedi hunters, as the bounty hunter [[Cad Bane]] was known for killing Jedi during the Clone Wars.<ref name="Cargo of Doom">{{TCW|Cargo of Doom}}</ref> The [[Sith assassin]] [[Ochi]] of [[Bestoon]] was a Jedi hunter who fought [[Jedi Master]]s [[Depa Billaba]] and [[Mace Windu]] during the war.<ref name="Shadow of the Sith">''[[Shadow of the Sith]]''</ref>

===Imperial Era===
{{Quote|In actuality, I would say the Jedi hunt themselves. Do you know the key to hunting a Jedi, friend? It is patience. Jedi cannot help what they are. Their compassion leaves a trail. For example, in our line of work, rumors run rampant. Here's one I heard just recently. It involves a Jedi hiding right here in your lovely saloon. Let's say ours is a wanderer. Maybe he's looking for people like him. Comes across this establishment. Nice place. And then he sees you. A man in need. Perhaps the locals are stealing from you. Threatening you. So what is the Jedi to do? Help you and risk exposure? Or move on? Now, if he were smart, he'd keep moving, but the Jedi Code is like an itch. He cannot help it. So he steps in and saves your saloon. You offer him a place to hide. Fresh water, shade from the suns, but the stories, they begin and they travel quickly. His compassion has been his undoing.|[[The Grand Inquisitor]]|<ref name="Part I">{{Kenobi|Part I}}</ref>}}
Following the [[Proclamation of the New Order|transformation]] of the Galactic Republic into the first [[Galactic Empire]], the [[Inquisitorius]] rose as an organization of Jedi hunters trained by [[Anakin Skywalker|Darth Vader]] to harness the [[dark side of the Force]] and wield [[double-bladed spinning lightsaber]]s as they assisted in the Empire's [[Great Jedi Purge|extermination]] of the Jedi.<ref name="beware">''[[Star Wars Rebels: Beware the Inquisitor!]]''</ref><ref name="Rise of the Old Masters">{{Rebels|Rise of the Old Masters}}</ref> [[Galactic Emperor]] [[Darth Sidious|Sheev Palpatine]] decreed that captured former members of the Jedi Order were to be converted into [[Inquisitor]]s, or otherwise be killed, further cementing the downfall of the Jedi [[religion]] and perversion of [[the Force]].<ref name="Fallen Order">''[[Star Wars Jedi: Fallen Order]]''</ref> Vader himself would also carry out hunts for Jedi, particularly for high-profile Jedi like [[Tensu Run]]<ref name="Inquisitors 4">[[Inquisitors 4|''Inquisitors'' 4]]</ref> and [[Obi-Wan Kenobi]].<ref name="Part VI">{{Kenobi|Part VI}}</ref>

Ochi also remained in the Emperor's employ.<ref name="Shadow of the Sith" /> He was sent to kill Sidious's [[Sith apprentice]] [[Anakin Skywalker|Darth Vader]] and manage to put up a fight against the damaged [[Sith Lord]] and former Jedi Knight.<ref name="Vader 6">[[Darth Vader (2020) 6|''Darth Vader'' (2020) 6]]</ref> During the [[New Republic Era]], Ochi battled with Jedi Master [[Luke Skywalker]] during the [[quest for Exegol]].<ref name="Shadow of the Sith" />

